{"type":"message","id":"781ebf17","parentId":"65810c93","timestamp":"2026-03-04T02:37:21.144Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"OK this one worked! It returned an API key error, which means the params were passed correctly. The issue is that for some tools like finnhub and ths_ifind, there seems to be some internal server issue with how the tool handles parameters, but for twelvedata it actually works and reaches the provider.\n\nThe issue with ths_ifind might be a server configuration issue. Let me try to execute a different Chinese stock data tool if available, or I can try a different approach.\n\nActually wait - let me try using twelvedata with Chinese stocks. Let me see what format Chinese stocks use for twelvedata - probably something like \"000001.SS\" or similar.\n\nActually, for Chinese stocks in Twelve Data, I believe the format might be like \"000001.SS\" for Shanghai and \"399001.SZ\" for Shenzhen. Let me try this.","thinkingSignature":"7683e9527f55b2acc2bf3893f70f9926b503fc4cbe6a1fd7d990369d20b504cc"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_z5ne2663y8ed_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cd ~/.openclaw/workspace && node -e \"\nconst API_BASE = 'https://qveris.ai/api/v1';\nconst API_KEY = process.env.QVERIS_API_KEY;\n\nasync function execute() {\n  const res = await fetch(\\`\\${API_BASE}/tools/execute\\`, {\n    method: 'POST',\n    headers: {\n      'Content-Type': 'application/json',\n      'Authorization': \\`Bearer \\${API_KEY}\\`\n    },\n    body: JSON.stringify({ \n      tool_id: 'twelvedata.quote.retrieve.v1.affbefe3', \n      params: { symbol: '000001.SS' }\n    })\n  });\n  const data = await res.json();\n  console.log(JSON.stringify(data, null, 2));\n}\n\nexecute();\n\"","timeout":30}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.5","usage":{"input":22458,"output":382,"cacheRead":13984,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":36824,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cache